r.s: Provides extra data structures and iterable/array functionality.
r.d: teds (Tentative Extra Data Structures) is a collection of data structures and iterable functionality
r.n: * Make SortedStrictSet/SortedStrictMap use a binary search tree (not yet a balanced tree). * Associate iterators on SortedStrictSet/SortedStrictMap with nodes of the tree. Invalidate iterators pointing to a node when that node of the set/map is removed. * Fix sorting order when instantiating StableSortedListSet/SortedStrictSet/SortedStrictMap from unsorted arrays.
